		<td><b>Re: What's happening with new MMC5 boards and flash devices?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Between the part where the PowerPak and Everdrive N8 only have 512KiB for PRG-ROM emulation, and the part where the MMC5 is a sufficiently complex beast that I strongly suspect that it can't fit in its entirety into INL's dual-XC9572L boards. If you know what subset of the MMC5 the game uses ... well, INL already answered. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />That said, it looks to me like the InviteNES might have 2MiB for both PRG and CHR? (<a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=9&amp;t=8781" class="postlink">their announcement to this forum</a>, see the two ICs labelled &quot;R1LV1616RSA&quot;) I don't know if they've changed that; it's an obvious place to cut costs.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


