	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Yeah, not happening. Also, AFAIK, Loopy's MMC5 isn't complete. It has enough functionality for some popular games to work (Castlevania III), but the real MMC5 has a shitload of features that were not implemented yet.</div><br />If I remember well, it runs Just Breed fine, which does use the &quot;shitload of features&quot; you're talking about.<br /><br />Just Breed uses ExGraphics mode all the time (there is not a single moment in the game where it's not used), uses the multiplier all the time, and use extra sound. As far as I know all of these worked.<br /><br />Just Breed doesn't use much scanline counting effects, but CV3 does, and it works fine as well.<br /><br />I think the only thing that may have gone unimplemented without breaking games is vertical split-screen scroll. Only Uchuu Keibitai SDF uses this. One would have to check how well it work on the power pak.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


